Introduction

AWIN, formerly known as TRY, is a South Korean boy group consisting of five members: K, Roan, Dam, Ziki, and Doyul. The group first introduced themselves to the public through pre-debut promotional activities in Japan, beginning on January 20, 2024. Following months of preparation and anticipation, AWIN officially debuted on February 16, 2025, with their single album Hashtag (#Cheese), marking the start of their journey in the music industry.
